# Terraform Core (Implementation)

- **Small diffs:** Prefer incremental changes. One logical change per edit session; avoid bundling unrelated resources or modules.
- **No scope creep:** Implement only what the task or design log specifies. Do not add new resources or modules unless explicitly asked.
- **State and drift:** Do not assume state is clean; note when plan may require refresh or state operations. Do not run apply in this workflow unless the user explicitly requests it.
- **Verification:** After edits, run from the relevant module or root: `terraform fmt -recursive -check` (then `terraform fmt -recursive` if needed), `terraform validate`. Optionally `terraform plan` (no apply). Fix any validation failures before considering the task done.
